<Author>BostonAustin
<Content>Not what we expected We chose the Bali Spirit Hotel based on the great reviews from other travelers and amazing photos posted on their website. We booked a 3-night Spirit and Relaxation package offered by the hotel. Upon arrival the hotel staff was very friendly and helped us settle into our room. After a 5-night stay on Sanur Beach, the standard room seemed very dull and unlike the photos we had seen online, the toilet did not flush, etc. Through our stay, the food offered by the resort, whether it be the complimentary breakfast, the poolside menu, or the romantic dinner included in our package, was terrible. We instead chose to eat the majority of our meals at the amazing restaurants in the town of Ubud. Our package included a couples massage which after arriving we were told could not be done together because they did not have two massage therapists on staff at the same time. Instead they insisted that we each schedule 1 1/2 hour massages separately while the other waited, very much taking away from the couples getaway that we had anticipated. We chose to skip this part of the package and received no compensation from the resort. The distance from town was nice although with close proximity to the road we did hear road traffic throughout our stay. We liked the distance from town and actually had a very nice moonlit walk one night from town to the resort. Overall, just not what we expected. 
