<Author>zuari
<Content>A tiny slice of heaven We spent 5 glorious nights in Ubud and thoroughly enjoyed our stay at Bali Spirit. We stayed in one of the Legong suites which gave us a view over the gorges that make up the hotel property. the rooms have aircon, though we turned ours on only briefly in the afternoon, after a long day out. Didn't need it at night. Our bed was huge and comfortable. Only problem was that the bath, which came with a tub, had no shower curtain. Breakfast was substantial if you wanted the American style, or flavorful and very adequate, if you went for Balinese. Either way it was very good; we got fruit, lots of coffee and warm smiles. As you'll see, it's the Balinese who make Bali really special. We thoroughly enjoyed and appreciated the servers and porters who made our visit so comfortable. I got a massage on premises, which was both very moderately priced and just fantastic by US standards. The hotel is located quite near the Monkey Forest, and a walk through that (about 15 mins) took us into the center of Ubud. I'd recommend trying this at least once; the forest is shaded and pretty cool, and you're thoroughly entertained by monkey antics. The hotel's shuttle service, which runs once every 2 hours or so, served us well the rest of the time. 
