<Author>JoeLikesBali
<Content>Mediocre We booked for three nights, but checked out after one night. It wasn't so awful, I suppose, but we stayed at the Tegal Sari for 3 nights right before (TS was fully booked after that, so we had to move) so we knew what other hotels in Ubud had to offer. Our room at Bali Spirit cost $100, twice as much as our Tegal Sari room, and it wasn't nearly as nice. It was so dark that it was hard to read in it at night. The bed looked nice, but it was hard and uncomfortable. The balcony was so small that there was room for two chairs facing each other across a small table, but you could not put the chairs next to each other. The river gorge is nice when you are right next to it, for example when you are in the restaurant, but when you are in your room you don't see it. You only see the tops of trees. There is a nearby bridge across the gorge which has a lot of traffic that you hear constantly. Extras, such as laundry and minibar, were much more expensive than in other places we stayed. The website mentions special Balinese outdoor shower. What a load of BS. The outdoor shower is an indoor shower with a 20 cm high hole cut in one of the walls to let the bugs and the heat in, but you certainly know you are indoors. There is in fact no proper shower. The whole room is the shower, so the whole floor gets wet when you shower and when you get up in the middle of the night to go to the bathroom you get back into bed with wet feet. The location is inconvenient. It is a very long walk to Ubud (maybe 45 minutes or more) and much of it is along a road that is not interesting, so you have to depend on the shuttles, which leave every hour or two and drop you at a centralized location. (Compare this to the Tegal Sari, which had a personal shuttle available at all times to take you wherever you wanted.) This makes it hard to go out to restaurants at night. When we told then we were leaving they quickly offered to discuss the price, but we told them that we just didn't like the room. We went to Artini 3, where we paid $45 for a room that we liked much more and that was available without booking ahead of time. 
