<Author>rozl
<Content>Sensational Spirit We have recently returned from the Bali Spirit  loved it! Travelling with two families (4 adults  5 children aged between 7  13 ) we arrived to a smiling welcome, cold drink  fresh towels. The first room we were given was not suitable (balustrading on balcony not safe for young children) so we were quickly allocated another room. As previously rated there are many stairs - very difficult for young children or the elderly.I cannot even describe how great the staff are - always friendly  smiling  happy to accomodate any requests. They also love to hang around  have a chat - the Spirit definately operates on Bali Time!Breakfast is very nice and we also ate lunch a few times - also very good. Also did the cooking class including market tour which was excellent. Pool  pool bar are great - have a laugh at the locals all coming down to the river for a bath at around 5pm. Massage was wonderful - very relaxing!The complimentary shuttle bus will take you into town at set times or you can hire it any other time for $10US for the whole bus ! ( 8 seater ). We ate at some fantastic restaurants including Casa Luna  Nomads ( also the place next to Nomads - can't remember the name ) and if you visit Ubud you will realise you are very spoilt for food up there! This tiny hotel set in the jungle on the cliff overlooking the river truly encompasses the Spirit of Bali  it's people - dont miss out !P.S. Anyone travelling to Bali regardless of where you stay - please take any old clothes, toys, books, school supplies with you  donate them ( there are many orphanages - google Bali Orphanages or contact me for details ) to these wonderful people who could really use a little of our help.Cheers Roz 
