<Author>Scotsmaninmalaysia
<Content>Tranquility in the Jungle The drive from the airport to Ubud through the streets of Denpasar may make you wonder if you've really arrived in a magical island. But soon you are clear of the urban sprawl and passing stone carving and carpentry workshops, compounds of the local villages and rice padis. Bali Spirit Hotel is beautifully perched on a steep hillside above a river. We had a River Villa with a 2 single bed bedroom alcove off the small lounge and a large double bed upstairs. The villa was beautifully finished in local stone and wood, with a lovely private open air shower/bathroom. The pool was a short walk through the well maintained gardens, with an adequate no. of loungers and a nice swim up bar, to partake of a Bintang beer in the late afternoon sun. There is a 3 or 4 times daily free mini bus run into Ubud, but its a really pleasant 15m walk from the hotel to the south end of the main street, Jalan Monkey Forest. The restaurant is nice but quiet as most guests head for the town to eat in the evening. Staff helpful and friendly. We would go back in a moment. Price for villa $99 night plus 21% tax, incl breakfast. Superb value for money. 
