<Content>Musty, moldy and dark (but friendly staff!) We stayed in everything from mosquito-filled bungalows with no hot water to a luxury beach resort during our time in Bali. We absolutely loved eveywhere EXCEPT Bali Spirit. It was dark and dingy and smelled awful! We had to leave after only one night. In that short time, the clothes I put in the closet turned damp and smelled like mildew. The bedspread was damp to the touch. The pillows were the worst of all, though. They smelled so bad that my husband and I couldn't use them. Good thing we don't have asthma. I even walked outside in the pitch-black darkness in the middle of the night just to get some fresh air. And the bathroom is dark and depressing. We love outdoor showers, but this one was just plain depressing. I hate to write a bad review, because the staff was SO FRIENDLY. They did their best to help us. They offered to move us to a room on the second floor, but it had the same problem--though not quite as bad. There was a strange sink in the room too. It was old and no longer hooked up to anything. Weird. The breakfast was not great. The grounds are GORGEOUS, but the location is not good. Sure, I like privacy and peacefulness, but that can be found in Ubud as well. You don't have to be in a river valley to experience Balinese nature. It's everywhere. The shuttle was not convenient at all. We felt trapped in our dungeonous dwelling. So sorry for the bad news. The good news is that we moved to a $30 a night room that was amazingly beautiful. The grounds were gorgeous and our view was heart-stopping. Much better hotels can be found for MUCH LESS MONEY. I promise. 
